3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex calculates funding rates hourly based on the 8-hour TWAP premium between perpetual and spot prices. The rate is exchanged between long and short positions at each settlement. Cross-margin is enabled by default, allowing efficient capital allocation across positions. The off-chain sequencer processes funding calculations rapidly while the on-chain risk engine ensures settlement integrity."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","UNI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"UNI perpetuals often exhibit elevated funding rates during DeFi sector rotations and governance events. As Uniswap's native token, UNI shows strong correlation with overall DEX volumes and L2 adoption trends. The combination of hourly settlements and low fees makes UNI/USDT attractive for short-term funding rate arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"UNI funding rates on Vertex typically range from -0.01% to 0.05% hourly during normal market conditions. Rates spike during major Uniswap protocol updates, governance proposals, or broader DeFi rallies. Weekly patterns show higher positive rates during US trading hours when DeFi activity peaks. Monthly analysis reveals funding rate correlation with UNI's price momentum and overall DeFi TVL changes."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex's hourly funding settlements create frequent arbitrage windows, especially during volatile DeFi market phases. Cross-margin functionality allows efficient hedging across multiple perpetual positions simultaneously. The platform's low latency sequencer enables rapid position adjustments when funding rate differentials emerge against other exchanges. Arbitrageurs can capitalize on UNI's tendency toward positive funding during bullish DeFi cycles."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex operates on a hybrid model where sequencer downtime could affect funding rate calculations temporarily. Arbitrum network congestion may impact settlement timing, though this is less common than on Ethereum mainnet. Cross-margin positions require careful monitoring as UNI's correlation with other DeFi tokens can amplify liquidation risks. The platform's concentrated liquidity on Arbitrum means large positions may face slippage during volatile periods."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are UNI funding rates settled on Vertex?","answer":"Vertex settles funding rates every hour for UNI/USDT perpetuals. The rate is calculated using an 8-hour time-weighted average premium and exchanged between long and short positions at each hourly settlement."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for UNI perpetuals on Vertex?","answer":"Vertex charges 0.02% for taker orders and 0.03% for maker orders on UNI/USDT perpetuals. These low fees make the platform particularly attractive for high-frequency funding rate arbitrage strategies."},{"question":"Does Vertex support cross-margin for UNI positions?","answer":"Yes, Vertex enables cross-margin by default for all perpetual positions including UNI/USDT. This allows traders to use their entire account balance as collateral across multiple positions, improving capital efficiency for arbitrage strategies."},{"question":"What risks come with Vertex's hybrid DEX model for UNI trading?","answer":"The main risks include potential sequencer downtime affecting order execution and funding calculations. Since Vertex is concentrated on Arbitrum, network issues could impact trading. However, the on-chain risk engine provides settlement security even if the off-chain components face issues."}]}]
